  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "freerdp security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for freerdp is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "FreeRDP is a client implementation of the Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) that follows Microsoft\u0026apos;s open specifications. This package provides the client applications xfreerdp.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nFreeRDP is a free implementation of the Remote Desktop Protocol. Prior to 3.24.0, Integer Underflow in update_read_cache_bitmap_order Function of FreeRDP's Core Library This vulnerability is fixed in 3.24.0.(CVE-2026-29776)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for freerdp is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "freerdp",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
